  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 30 for SLE 12 SP5)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.12.14-122_116 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2022-20154: Fixed a use after free due to a race condition in lock_sock_nested of sock.c. This could lead to local escalation of privilege with System execution privileges needed (bsc#1200599).\n- CVE-2022-21499: Reinforced the kernel lockdown feature, until now it's been trivial to break out of it with kgdb or kdb (bsc#1199426).\n- CVE-2022-1729: Fixed a sys_perf_event_open() race condition against self (bsc#1199507).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
